detail.content: NYU > Department of German >         Sean Larson                                                                                                                                                 Back to Previous Page                 Sean Larson   Ph.D. candidate   Email:             Biography:   Sean studied Political Theory and  Philosophy at the Ludwig-Maximilians Universität in Munich as well as German and  Spanish Literature at the University of Florida, where his thesis examined  Adorno’s Negative Dialectics and the deficiency of its reception by the next  generation of the Frankfurt School. His research interests include Marxism,  aesthetic theory, psychoanalysis, Machiavelli, Brecht, and revolution. His  current work investigates the German Revolution of 1918-19 and its formative  effects on social and intellectual life in the Weimar Republic.                  Update your faculty profile

NYU > Department of German >         Sean Larson                                                                                                                                                 Back to Previous Page                 Sean Larson   Ph.D. candidate   Email:             Biography:   Sean studied Political Theory and  Philosophy at the Ludwig-Maximilians Universität in Munich as well as German and  Spanish Literature at the University of Florida, where his thesis examined  Adorno’s Negative Dialectics and the deficiency of its reception by the next  generation of the Frankfurt School. His research interests include Marxism,  aesthetic theory, psychoanalysis, Machiavelli, Brecht, and revolution. His  current work investigates the German Revolution of 1918-19 and its formative  effects on social and intellectual life in the Weimar Republic.                  Update your faculty profile
